message.content:
cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper is about Software-defined networking (SDN) and its data plane architecture. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as security is an important aspect of SDN and may be discussed in the paper. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as SDN involves control and management of network resources. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as SDN can be used in data center networks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category as the paper focuses more on the software aspect of SDN.
